abstract: PBS does music, with specials highlighting Bing Crosby, Bruce Springsteen and Peter, Paul & Mary.
snippet: PBS does music, with specials highlighting Bing Crosby, Bruce Springsteen and Peter, Paul & Mary.
lead_paragraph: You’ve probably never wondered what would happen if PBS were to merge with MTV, or at least with the MTV of yore, the one that was defined by music. But you can get a glimpse of that mythical hybrid this week as PBS lets its hair down.

abstract: New holiday music albums include ones from Idina Menzel, Irvin Mayfield, Darius Rucker, the Blind Boys of Alabama and the cast of “Downton Abbey.”
snippet: New holiday music albums include ones from Idina Menzel, Irvin Mayfield, Darius Rucker, the Blind Boys of Alabama and the cast of “Downton Abbey.”
lead_paragraph: THE holidays are a time for family, for reflection, for conspicuous consumption. For musicians, they’re a time to tackle old standards and see who comes out on top, or to try to record new ones, because there’s no bigger gift than hubris. Here, the pop and jazz critics of The New York Times reach down into their stockings and hope there’s no coal. (Prices may vary, depending on whether you’ve been naughty or nice.) JON CARAMANICA

abstract: At “Blank! The Musical,” the audience helps score, script, cast, direct and choreograph a one-performance-only production.
snippet: At “Blank! The Musical,” the audience helps score, script, cast, direct and choreograph a one-performance-only production.
lead_paragraph: Anybody know a surefire cure for getting rid of an earworm — one of those insistent tunes that play on and on in your head until you start smashing things? I’ve been invaded by a really clingy one. It’s the title song of “Directing One Direction,” and even listening to excruciatingly adhesive highlights from “The Phantom of the Opera” has failed to dislodge it.

abstract: Seven actors draw on their adolescence to animate “Punk Rock,” a drama about the power, vulnerability and confusion of youth, set at a private school in England.
snippet: Seven actors draw on their adolescence to animate “Punk Rock,” a drama about the power, vulnerability and confusion of youth, set at a private school in England.
lead_paragraph: Stagehands were still cleaning blood spatter from the walls of the “Punk Rock” set when seven members of its cast bounded into the lobby on a recent Thursday night. They’d quickly changed from soiled prep school uniforms into clean street clothes and traded British accents for American ones, except for Lilly Englert, who comes by her London intonations naturally.

abstract: Grim new productions in the British capital include “’Tis Pity She’s a Whore,” “Wildefire” and “Hippolytos.”
snippet: Grim new productions in the British capital include “’Tis Pity She’s a Whore,” “Wildefire” and “Hippolytos.”
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Maybe it’s the advent of winter in a city that gets dark at 4 p.m., but the London stage of late is laying on darkness with a vengeance, offering up body parts on skewers and illicit love gone awry.

abstract: The auto supplier began using ammonium nitrate in airbags in 2001, but the compound is highly sensitive to temperature changes and can combust violently.
snippet: The auto supplier began using ammonium nitrate in airbags in 2001, but the compound is highly sensitive to temperature changes and can combust violently.
lead_paragraph: The new airbag propellant was supposed to be the next big thing for Takata in 1998. An engineer for the company, Paresh Khandhadia, declared it “the new technological edge” in an interview with a trade magazine then.

headline_main: Keystone Vote Unlikely to Change Odds for Mary Landrieu

abstract: As senators prepare to vote Tuesday, Senator Mary L. Landrieu, Democrat of Louisiana, hopes her effort will help her in a close runoff election.
snippet: As senators prepare to vote Tuesday, Senator Mary L. Landrieu, Democrat of Louisiana, hopes her effort will help her in a close runoff election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Mary L. Landrieu of Louisiana continued to work on Tuesday to round up votes for the Keystone XL oil pipeline, part of a last-minute effort to help her survive a close runoff and one of the toughest battles of her political career.
